    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.111-112_0001b"/>
                
                <opener>
                    <hi rend="caps">DEAR DR NEIHARDT,</hi>
                </opener>
                <p><hi rend="caps">THERE IS THE STATEMENT "BETTER NEVER THAN LATE." HOWEVER I DO NOT BELONG TO THIS SCHOOL OF THOUGHT ... I AM WRITING THIS NOTE BECAUSE I KNOW MY EXPRESSION OF GRATEFULNESS IS BETTER LATE THAN NEVER.</hi></p>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">111</fw>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.111-112_0002"/>
                
                <p><hi rend="caps">PERHAPS YOU FELT MY APPRECIATION THE EVENING I VISITED WITH YOU ABOUT THE VERSE I BROUGHT ALONG. IT WAS A PRIVILEGE TO SPEAK WITH YOU AND I CAN UNDERSTAND WHY THERE IS ADMIRATION FOR YOU AMONG THE PEOPLE IN COLUMBIA.</hi></p>
                
                <note type="curatorial"><hi rend="caps">JOHN G. NEIHARDT CENTER</hi></note>
                
                <p><hi rend="caps">PLEASE KNOW MY DEEP AND SINCERE ENJOYMENT OF THE TIME YOU GAVE ME. YOUR THOUGHTFUL REMARKS GAVE ME FRESH ENCOURAGEMENT, AND PERHAPS MOST OF ALL THIS IS THE IMPORTANCE OF PASSING ON TO OTHERS WHAT WE KNOW AND WHAT WE FEEL.</hi></p>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.111-112_0001a"/>
                
                <p><hi rend="caps">IF I SHOULD BE IN COLUMBIA THIS FALL I HOPE I CAN ENROLL IN EPIC AMERICA OR SOMEONE OF THE COURSES WHICH WILL GIVE ME MORE OF YOUR PERSONALITY AND INFLUENCE.</hi></p>
                <closer>
                    <salute><hi rend="caps">SINCERELY,</hi></salute>
                
                    <signed>BIRDINA HOSPERS</signed>
                
                    <dateline><hi rend="caps">JUNE NINETEENTH</hi></dateline>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
            <div1 type="envelope">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.111-112_0003"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">112</fw>
                
                <ab type="postmark">
                    COLUMBIA, <unclear cert="high">MO.</unclear>
                    JUN 20
                    3-PM
                    1958
                
                    PRAY
                    FOR
                    PEACE
                </ab>
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>3 Cent Stamp</figDesc>
                    <p>U.S. POSTAGE 3Â¢
                    IN GOD WE TRUST
                    LIBERTY</p>
                </figure>
                
                <ab type="address">
                    <address>
                        <addrLine><hi rend="caps">DR JOHN G NEIHARDT</hi></addrLine>
